  "statement": {
    "title": "torch.linalg.vector_norm overflows for large-ord scalar inputs via pow-then-root",
    "body": "`torch._refs.linalg.vector_norm` computes `pow(reduce_sum(pow(x, ord)), 1/ord)`. For a scalar input (single element) with large `ord`, `pow(x, ord)` overflows to inf even though the result should be `abs(x)`. Eager `torch.linalg.vector_norm` correctly short-circuits the scalar case. Fix: add an early-exit for scalar (single-element) inputs that returns `abs(x)` directly without the pow-then-root path.",
    "labels": ["module: linalg", "topic: numerical"]
  },
  "operator": {
